# Android release signing — copy this to `android/key.properties` (gitignored)
# and fill in real values to produce a SIGNED release .aab/.apk.
#
# 1. Generate a one-time UPLOAD keystore (keep it safe + backed up; losing it
#    means you can never update the app unless you enrolled in Play App Signing):
#
#      keytool -genkeypair -v \
#        -keystore ~/profitsync-upload.jks \
#        -alias upload -keyalg RSA -keysize 2048 -validity 9125
#
#    Store the .jks OUTSIDE the repo (anywhere gitignored). *.jks/*.keystore are
#    gitignored, but keeping it out of the tree entirely is safest.
#
# 2. Point storeFile at its ABSOLUTE path and set the passwords/alias you chose.
#
# 3. Recommended: enrol the app in **Play App Signing** (Play Console does this on
#    first upload). Google then holds the real app-signing key; this file's
#    keystore is only your *upload* key, which Google lets you reset if lost.
#
# See docs/native/SIGNING.md for the full walkthrough.

storeFile=/absolute/path/to/profitsync-upload.jks
storePassword=CHANGE_ME
keyAlias=upload
keyPassword=CHANGE_ME
